This is the [talk page](/Wikipedia:Talk_page_guidelines) for discussing improvements to the [Bank](/Bank) article. It's not some dusty archive for historical grievances, but a living space for refining the very essence of what a bank is. And no, this is not a forum for your personal gripes about your mortgage or the barista at your local branch. Stick to the article, or find a more appropriate outlet for your existential angst.

### New to Wikipedia? Welcome!

If you're new here, take a moment to breathe. Learn to edit; get help. It's not rocket science, though sometimes it feels like it, trying to inject a modicum of sense into the chaos. Remember to [assume good faith](/Wikipedia:Assume_good_faith), be polite, and for the love of all that's logical, avoid personal attacks. And please, try not to bite the newcomers, though I make no promises about the tone of your eventual interactions. If you find yourself in a vortex of disagreement, seek [dispute resolution](/Wikipedia:Dispute_resolution_requests). It's a process, and like most processes, it’s likely to be tedious.

### Article policies

We operate under certain guiding principles: a [neutral point of view](/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view), a strict adherence to [no original research](/Wikipedia:No_original_research), and an unwavering commitment to [verifiability](/Wikipedia:Verifiability). If you can't back it up with a source, don't bother.

